Demand immediate liquidation of outstanding cash advances;


Prepare demand letters to be issued to concerned officers and employees for cash advances that remained unliquidated/unsettled for more than 30 days;

Strengthen the operation of preventive and monitoring controls to ensure timely submission of liquidation documents;

Undertake, as a last resort, appropriate legal actions for the recovery and/or settlement of unliquidated cash advances;

Initiate the filing of request for the write off of outstanding balance of deceased employees from the Commission on Audit.

